001package squidpony.squidmath;
002
003/**
004 * A group of similar methods for getting hashes of points based on long coordinates in 2, 3, 4, or 6 dimensions and
005 * a long for state. Internally, the methods here are based on a simplified version of Hive from {@link CrossHash};
006 * this version does not include the somewhat-involved finalization step. Omitting finalization helps this class be
007 * somewhat faster, but also makes it so it doesn't avalanche very well. Avalanche refers to the property of a hash
008 * where one changed bit in the input(s) or state has a chance to change any of the output's bits, and should
009 * usually change about 50% of them. You can call {@link #avalanche(long)} on the result of a hashAll() call to put
010 * the finalization step back. This has rather good quality when {@link #avalanche(long)} is used, but most usage
011 * will not be able to discern a difference between the quality of this (with or without avalanche) and the quality of
012 * {@link HastyPointHash}, where HastyPointHash is a fair amount faster. If your state and input are ints anyway,
013 * consider {@link IntPointHash}, since it's faster than the long-based hashes and still has perfectly fine quality.
014 * <br>
015 * This implements {@link IPointHash} and has a long it uses internally for state, exposed by {@link #getState()}.
016 */
017public final class PointHash extends IPointHash.LongImpl
018{
019    @Override
020    public int hashWithState(int x, int y, int state) {
021        return (int)hashAll(x, y, state);
022    }
023
024    @Override
025    public int hashWithState(int x, int y, int z, int state) {
026        return (int)hashAll(x, y, z, state);
027    }
028
029    @Override
030    public int hashWithState(int x, int y, int z, int w, int state) {
031        return (int)hashAll(x, y, z, w, state);
032    }
033
034    @Override
035    public int hashWithState(int x, int y, int z, int w, int u, int state) {
036        return (int)hashAll(x, y, z, w, u, state);
037    }
038    @Override
039    public int hashWithState(int x, int y, int z, int w, int u, int v, int state) {
040        return (int)hashAll(x, y, z, w, u, v, state);
041    }
042
043    public long getState(){
044        return state;
045    }
046
047    /**
048     * If it's important for some usage that one bit of change in any parameters cause roughly 50% of all bits in
049     * the result to change, then you can call this on the output of any hashAll() overload to improve the bit
050     * avalanche qualities.
051     * @param state the output of hashAll() in this class
052     * @return a significantly-mixed-around long obtained from state
053     */
054    public static long avalanche(long state)
055    {
056        state = (state ^ state >>> 33) * 0xFF51AFD7ED558CCDL;
057        return (state ^ state >>> 33) * 0xC4CEB9FE1A85EC53L;
058    }
059    /**
060     *
061     * @param x
062     * @param y
063     * @param state
064     * @return 64-bit hash of the x,y point with the given state
065     */
066    public static long hashAll(long x, long y, long state)
067    {
068        state *= 0x9E3779B97F4A7C15L;
069        long other = 0x60642E2A34326F15L;
070        state ^= (other += (x ^ 0xC6BC279692B5CC85L) * 0x6C8E9CF570932BABL);
071        state = (state << 54 | state >>> 10);
072        state ^= (other += (y ^ 0xC6BC279692B5CC85L) * 0x6C8E9CF570932BABL);
073        state -= ((state << 54 | state >>> 10) + (other ^ other >>> 29)) * 0x94D049BB133111EBL;
074        return state ^ state >>> 31;
075

079//                                    | 1L)) ^ y >>> 24) 
080//                            | 1L)) ^ x >>> 24);

178    /**

180     * @param x
181     * @param y

187     */
188    public static long hashAll(long x, long y, long z, long w, long u, long state)
189    {
190        state *= 0x9E3779B97F4A7C15L;
191        long other = 0x60642E2A34326F15L;
192        state ^= (other += (x ^ 0xC6BC279692B5CC85L) * 0x6C8E9CF570932BABL);
193        state = (state << 54 | state >>> 10);
194        state ^= (other += (y ^ 0xC6BC279692B5CC85L) * 0x6C8E9CF570932BABL);
195        state = (state << 54 | state >>> 10);
196        state ^= (other += (z ^ 0xC6BC279692B5CC85L) * 0x6C8E9CF570932BABL);
197        state = (state << 54 | state >>> 10);
198        state ^= (other += (w ^ 0xC6BC279692B5CC85L) * 0x6C8E9CF570932BABL);
199        state = (state << 54 | state >>> 10);
200        state ^= (other += (u ^ 0xC6BC279692B5CC85L) * 0x6C8E9CF570932BABL);
201        state -= ((state << 54 | state >>> 10) + (other ^ other >>> 29)) * 0x94D049BB133111EBL;
202        return state ^ state >>> 31;
